The '''Minority Affairs Department''' is a [[Ministry (government department)|department]] of the [[Government of Sindh]], [[Pakistan]]. It was established in the 1995 with the religions Affairs, Auqaf, Zakat and Ushr departments, but became a separate department in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sindh.gov.pk/dpt/MinorityAffairs/index.htm |title=Minority Affairs Department Govt of Sindh |publisher=Sindh.gov.pk |date= |accessdate=2014-07-20}}</ref>
The department was created to safeguard the rights of minorities and facilitates in the formulation of overall policy, planning, coordination, evaluation and review of the regulatory framework.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sindh.gov.pk/dpt/MinorityAffairs/goalsobjective.htm |title=Minority Affairs Department Govt of Sindh |publisher=Sindh.gov.pk |date= |accessdate=2014-07-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sindh.gov.pk/dpt/MinorityAffairs/visionmission.htm |title=Minority Affairs Department Govt of Sindh |publisher=Sindh.gov.pk |date= |accessdate=2014-07-20}}</ref>
